This paper is about training low-precision neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a new methodology for training neural networks. The second likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper evaluates the proposed method on image classification tasks. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with optimizing neural network performance. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper proposes a new method for training neural networks. The fifth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper deals with the optimization of neural network weights.
